  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (0ae39ea 2023-12-11T00:27:32.487222000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge coverage\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`forge coverage` ignores the `config.toml` file for invariant tests. \r\n\r\nInvariant testing in coverage mode thus uses the default 256 runs which is small, making coverage for big invariant tests (eg. using handlers) noisy/useless. This is not the case for regular (non-invariant) tests. Such a feature would bring us closer to #4007. ",
